{{item:3111}} 

As silly as this is it's actually kinda true... you only need 1 item to beat him in lane...with his stun now on a delay its really easy to dodge with a little bit of extra movement speed.... then with the tenacity even if you get stunned you can still always dodge his W... so at most he can burn his ult on you and land his Q and probably not get a kill off it or even do enough damage to force you to back... so really all he can really do is zone you and deny farm

obviously this is satirical but it does illustrate the some of the problems with Veigar

